Windows
- Clean Start Menu with cmd command: reg add "HKCU\Software\Microsoft\Windows\CurrentVersion\Policies\Explorer" /v NoStartMenuMorePrograms /t REG_DWORD /d 1 /f && taskkill /f /im explorer.exe && start explorer.exe
- Disable virtualized Windows security (Memory integrity), Disable "Enhance pointer precision", Install AMD chipset and GPU drivers. First disable fast startup, than disable hibernation in CMD: powercfg -h off.
- Create 32-bit DWORD named RealTimeIsUniversal in "HKEY_LOCAL_MACHINE\System\CurrentControlSet\Control\TimeZoneInformation" and assign value 1. Reason: Sync Linux and Windows time.
- Set password in Powershell (Set-LocalUser -Name "Username" -Password (ConvertTo-SecureString "Password" -AsPlainText -Force)
- Lock apps:
  - Group Policy:
    1.) Computer Config → Windows Settings → Security Settings → Local Policies → Security Options → UAC: Behavior of the elevation prompt for administrators in Admin Approval Mode (Set to: Prompt for credentials)
    2.) Computer Config → Windows Settings → Security Settings → Local Policies → Security Options → UAC: Admin Approval Mode for the Built-in Administrator account (Set to: Enabled)
  - Add or Remove applications:
    - Add: .exe program Compatibility → Change settings for all users → Run this program as an administrator
    - Remove: Create New Task Scheduler Task → Check "Run with highest privileges → Actions: Run .exe program → Create a shortcut with target: C:\Windows\System32\schtasks.exe /run /tn "Task Scheduler Task Name"
  - Set wallpaper with password 
- Gaming optimizations: 
  1.) AMD Adrenalin Software
      - Graphics:
        - Wait for Vertical Refresh: Always on
      - Display Settings:
        - Adaptive Sync Compatible: Disabled
  2.) Lossless Scaling Frame Generation
      - Frame Generation: 
        - Type: LSFG 3.1 (or newer), Mode: Adaptive, Target: 165, Flow Scale: 75%, Performance Mode: Off
      - Capture:
        - Capture API: DXGI, Queue Target: 1
      - Rendering: 
        - Sync Mode: Off (Allow tearing), Max frame latency: 3, HDR support: Off, G-Sync support: Off, Draw FPS: On
  3.) In-Game 
      - Enable 165 FPS limit, if possible
      - Enable upscaling, if needed (FSR / OptiScaler, etc.)
- Launch at startup: MSI Afterburner (-30mV, -30% Power, 50°C → 15% Fan, 60°C → 100% Fan), LSFG (via Task Scheduler on workstation unlock) and Steam (""C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steam.exe" -silent" shortcut)


Arch Linux
- KDE Plasma (Disable KDE Wallet: ~./config/ -> open kwalletrc file -> set Enabled=false). Disable all desktop effects. Add --disable-pinch to all "Exec=" in brave-browser.desktop.
- Insert these lines into etc/environment: PLASMA_USE_QT_SCALING=1, QT_SCALE_FACTOR_ROUNDING_POLICY=RoundPreferFloor, FREETYPE_PROPERTIES="cff:no-stem-darkening=0 autofitter:no-stem-darkening=0"
- Display settings: Display Scaling 125% (150% on Laptop), RGB Range: Full, Color Accuracy: Prefer color accuracy, Put to sleep: After 30 min
- Font settings: 11pt except small 9pt, Anti-aliasing: Enable, Sub-Pixel rendering: RGB, Hinting: Full
- Disable pointer acceleration. Touchpad: 0.6 speed and 2nd slowest scroll speed. Desktop mouse: -0.2 speed
- Run in Konsole: timedatectl set-local-rtc 1 --adjust-system-clock. Reason: Sync Linux and Windows time.
